										<span>The objective of the Monitoring and Evaluation tool is to:</span>
										<div><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i><span> Assist the HWSETA in monitoring and valuation of projects funded from discretionary grants</span></div>
										<div><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i><span> Ascertain the progress of the project and whether HWSETA should continue releasing funds to the organisation mandated to deliver the project.</span></div>
									</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="avoid_page_break">
									<td class="me_head_underline">Requirements for M and E</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="avoid_page_break">
									<td class="padding_20">
										<div><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i><span> An MOA / MOU between the organisation being funded and the HWSETA.</span></div>
										<div><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i><span> The funded organisation must have submitted proof of commencement of the project.</span></div>
										<div><span> e.g. Learnership agreements, learner list, proof of registration with a TVET or University.</span></div>
										<div><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i><span> The HWSETA must have disbursed part of the total funding to the employer / organisation</span></div>
										<div><i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i><span> The employer must have submitted to the HWSETA an employer report</span></div>
									</td>
								</tr>
